From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: developers <developers@tuxbox-neutrino.org>
Date: Thu, 5 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] tuxcom: enable GetRCCode for generic hardware

Generic builds define HAVE_GENERIC_HARDWARE but the RC handler was
only compiled for legacy STB hardware. This makes GetRCCode undefined
and breaks the plugin link.

Treat generic hardware like the existing evdev-based RC paths.
---
 tuxcom.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/tuxcom.c
+++ b/tuxcom.c
@@ -40,7 +40,7 @@ static int sync_blitter = 0;
 /******************************************************************************
  * GetRCCode  (Code from Tuxmail)
  ******************************************************************************/
 
-#if defined HAVE_CST_HARDWARE || HAVE_TRIPLEDRAGON || HAVE_SPARK_HARDWARE || defined(HAVE_DUCKBOX_HARDWARE) || HAVE_ARM_HARDWARE
+#if defined HAVE_CST_HARDWARE || HAVE_TRIPLEDRAGON || HAVE_SPARK_HARDWARE || defined(HAVE_DUCKBOX_HARDWARE) || HAVE_ARM_HARDWARE || defined(HAVE_GENERIC_HARDWARE)
 int GetRCCode()
 {
 	static int count = 0;
-- 
2.43.0
